1967;;Come Spy with Me;;American;;Marshall Stone;;Troy Donahue, Andrea Dromm, Albert Dekker;;spy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Come_Spy_with_Me_(film);;Starring Troy Donahue and Andrea Dromm, the film features Dromm ("I'm an AGENT, not a spy!"), solving a murder case, rescuing a kidnap victim (Valerie Allen, Donahue's wife at the time of filming), breaking up a mastermind's (Albert Dekker) underwater bomb assassination plot of several world leaders, and dancing the new dance called "the Shark" on the Caribbean island of Jamaica.[1] Smokey Robinson & the Miracles performed the film's titular theme song, written by lead singer Robinson.